sense of self-consciousness,

00:01:58.820 --> 00:02:00.210
they vanish completely.

00:02:00.210 --> 00:02:02.380
Time dilates, which is
a fancy way of saying it

00:02:02.380 --> 00:02:03.710
passes strangely.

00:02:03.710 --> 00:02:06.400
So sometimes it speeds
up, and five hours

00:02:06.400 --> 00:02:07.810
will go by in five minutes.

00:02:07.810 --> 00:02:10.082
And occasionally it
slows down, and you'll

00:02:10.082 --> 00:02:12.040
get that freeze-frame
effect-- maybe any of you

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:14.590
have been in a car crash
or seen "The Matrix."

00:02:14.590 --> 00:02:17.300
And throughout, all
aspects of performance--

00:02:17.300 --> 00:02:20.450
that's mental and physical--
go through the roof.

00:02:20.450 --> 00:02:23.220
And if you want a quick
and dirty definition of it,

00:02:23.220 --> 00:02:25.950
flow is as close to
picture-perfect decision

00:02:25.950 --> 00:02:28.140
making as we can
possibly get, which is

00:02:28.140 --> 00:02:29.560
where the state gets its name.

00:02:29.560 --> 00:02:32.150
In the state of
flow, every decision,

00:02:32.150 --> 00:02:35.390
every action leads seamlessly,
fluidly, perfectly,

00:02:35.390 --> 00:02:36.000
to the next.

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:37.670
Flow feels flowy.

00:02:37.670 --> 00:02:39.577
So it's actually
a technical term.

00:02:39.577 --> 00:02:41.410
It came out of, actually,
one of the largest

00:02:41.410 --> 00:02:42.760
psychological studies ever done.

00:02:42.760 --> 00:02:44.968
And when they were interviewing
people, about it they

00:02:44.968 --> 00:02:46.360
kept using this term, flow.

00:02:46.360 --> 00:02:48.400
So that's where it came from.

00:02:48.400 --> 00:02:50.540
