00:47:34.450 --> 00:47:36.740
But they're nonspecific
amplifiers of consciousness.

00:47:36.740 --> 00:47:39.410
So what really sculpts
the psychedelic trip

00:47:39.410 --> 00:47:41.256
is your set and your setting.

00:47:41.256 --> 00:47:42.880
So the setting is
the place that you've

00:47:42.880 --> 00:47:44.710
pre-configured, that
you've architected,

00:47:44.710 --> 00:47:46.300
where the trip is
going to unfold.

00:47:46.300 --> 00:47:47.841
And of course, the
set is what you're

00:47:47.841 --> 00:47:49.510
bringing to that--
your predispositions,

00:47:49.510 --> 00:47:51.700
your fears, your
anxieties, your intention,

00:47:51.700 --> 00:47:55.180
what you want to resolve, what
you want to probe and explore.

00:47:55.180 --> 00:47:58.520
And what you come to
perceive in those moments,

00:47:58.520 --> 00:48:00.910
according to the work of
Rich Doyle, who I adore,

00:48:00.910 --> 00:48:02.760
is that you come
to perceive, first

00:48:02.760 --> 00:48:04.571
of all, the feedback
loops between

00:48:04.571 --> 00:48:07.070
your creative and linguistic
choices and your consciousness.

00:48:07.070 --> 00:48:08.611
In other words, once
the trip starts,

00:48:08.611 --> 00:48:10.250
you realize just how
much where you are

00:48:10.250 --> 00:48:13.070
is determining your
subjective experience.

00:48:13.070 --> 00:48:15.610
If you're in a mystical,
beautiful park in Big Sur,

00:48:15.610 --> 00:48:18.450
you start to feel mystical,
beautiful sensations.

00:48:18.450 --> 00:48:20.650
But you're feeling those
already unconsciously just

00:48:20.650 --> 00:48:21.590
by being there.

00:48:21.590 --> 00:48:24.610
But the trip, in amplifying
and bringing forth

00:48:24.610 --> 00:48:26.865
that subconscious feeling,
all of a sudden the theater

00:48:26.865 --> 00:48:30.880
of the moment is informed
by the stage that you're in.

00:48:30.880 --> 00:48:32.630
So if you're in that
beautiful place,

00:48:32.630 --> 00:48:35.890
it's already coloring the
trip towards beautiful spaces.

00:48:35.890 --> 00:48:37.470
If you pre-configure
music-- there's

00:48:37.470 --> 00:48:38.928
an article by
Timothy Leary written

00:48:38.928 --> 00:48:42.092
in the '60s called "Programming
the Psychedelic Experience."

00:48:42.092 --> 00:48:44.550
Which was all about the idea
