00:49:09.050 --> 00:49:10.650
and make the return.

00:49:10.650 --> 00:49:14.000
And holy moly, talk about
compressing a journey

00:49:14.000 --> 00:49:14.906
into a journey.

00:49:14.906 --> 00:49:16.530
But I think this is
really fascinating.

00:49:16.530 --> 00:49:17.700
You can tell I'm very
passionate about this.

00:49:17.700 --> 00:49:18.840
STEVEN KOTLER: Jason Silva,
ladies and gentlemen.

00:49:18.840 --> 00:49:20.530
JASON SILVA: No, no.

00:49:20.530 --> 00:49:22.450
But there's a lot to do here.

00:49:22.450 --> 00:49:25.690
But really, the key idea
is that consciousness

00:49:25.690 --> 00:49:28.960
is a collaborative act
between subject and object.

00:49:28.960 --> 00:49:31.510
And it becomes even more
so a collaborative act

00:49:31.510 --> 00:49:34.760
between subject and object when
you are in a psychedelically

00:49:34.760 --> 00:49:35.670
addled state.

00:49:35.670 --> 00:49:38.310
You realize that
mind, that awareness,

00:49:38.310 --> 00:49:41.050
is a co-production
between self and world.

00:49:41.050 --> 00:49:42.990
It's all about
these feedback loops

00:49:42.990 --> 00:49:45.110
that you just come to
witness and you come to see.

00:49:45.110 --> 00:49:47.530
So that can either be
a frightening bummer

00:49:47.530 --> 00:49:49.470
if you're in the
wrong set and setting,

00:49:49.470 --> 00:49:54.390
or can be nirvana in the
right set and setting.

00:49:54.390 --> 00:49:56.582
STEVEN KOTLER: What Jason said.

00:49:56.582 --> 00:49:58.199
I don't know how to follow that.

00:49:58.199 --> 00:50:00.240
JASON SILVA: OK, we've
got a couple more minutes.

00:50:00.240 --> 00:50:00.740
Any?

00:50:00.740 --> 00:50:01.690
Yes.

00:50:01.690 --> 00:50:04.219
