00:50:19.031 --> 00:50:20.030
STEVEN KOTLER: Oh, yeah.

00:50:20.030 --> 00:50:22.960
So I said earlier,
there's a flow cycle.

00:50:22.960 --> 00:50:25.240
The first part of the
cycle is known as struggle.

00:50:25.240 --> 00:50:28.060
And it is-- your prefrontal
cortex may go away in flow.

00:50:28.060 --> 00:50:29.950
This is all prefrontal cortex.

00:50:29.950 --> 00:50:31.730
Struggle is called
struggle for a reason.

00:50:31.730 --> 00:50:32.940
It is really unpleasant.

00:50:32.940 --> 00:50:34.290
It is a learning phase.

00:50:34.290 --> 00:50:35.362
It is a loading phase.

00:50:35.362 --> 00:50:37.820
You are loading and overloading
the brain with information.

00:50:41.750 --> 00:50:45.690
