00:56:59.650 --> 00:57:00.980
You don't need physical risk.

00:57:00.980 --> 00:57:03.240
You can replace it
with emotional risk,

00:57:03.240 --> 00:57:04.880
intellectual risk,
or social risk.

00:57:04.880 --> 00:57:07.310
And the cool thing
is social risk,

00:57:07.310 --> 00:57:09.840
your brain can't
tell the difference

00:57:09.840 --> 00:57:11.990
between physical danger
and social danger.

00:57:11.990 --> 00:57:14.980
They're processed in the
exact same structures.

00:57:14.980 --> 00:57:17.010
Which is why fear
of public speaking

00:57:17.010 --> 00:57:18.530
is the number one
fear in the world,

00:57:18.530 --> 00:57:20.490
and not, say, getting
eaten by a grizzly bear.

00:57:20.490 --> 00:57:22.580
You would think from an
evolutionary perspective,

00:57:22.580 --> 00:57:25.160
getting eaten by a grizzly
bear is something scary.

00:57:25.160 --> 00:57:26.670
But no, it's public speaking.

00:57:26.670 --> 00:57:29.720
And the reason is if
you go back 300 years,

00:57:29.720 --> 00:57:32.600
and you screwed up socially,
you get kicked out.

00:57:32.600 --> 00:57:33.640
Kicked out of the tribe.

00:57:33.640 --> 00:57:34.160
Exiled.

00:57:34.160 --> 00:57:34.659
Banished.

00:57:34.659 --> 00:57:35.750
Capital punishment.

00:57:35.750 --> 00:57:38.430
So the brain can't tell the
difference between social fear

00:57:38.430 --> 00:57:39.510
and physical fear.

00:57:39.510 --> 00:57:42.980
So being on stage-- even if
you do it a lot-- it definitely

00:57:42.980 --> 00:57:44.447
focuses you a lot.

00:57:44.447 --> 00:57:45.530
And I think Jason's right.

00:57:45.530 --> 00:57:47.320
I don't feel entitled
anybody's time.

00:57:47.320 --> 00:57:50.060
So I don't want
to bore you guys.

00:57:50.060 --> 00:57:52.898
So that helps drive
attention, as well.

